# Next.js / React

- Use the **App Router** layout under **`apps/frontend/app/`** with `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx` as appropriate.
- Prefer **named exports** for components when the file already follows that pattern; stay consistent with neighboring files.
- Keep frontend layer separation strict:
  - `.tsx` files are for view structure/composition.
  - `.ts` files are for reusable logic/helpers (formatters, selectors, mappers).
  - Web styles live in `.css`/`.module.css`.
- **Web UI**: Shared DOM components live in **`@portfolio/storybook`** (`packages/storybook/src/`). Import from the app as **`@portfolio/storybook`** (and package CSS subpaths). Do not add new `components/` for web UI; ESLint enforces this.
- **Presentational JSX and CSS belong in Storybook**: **`apps/frontend/app/**/*.tsx`** route segments (`page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `error.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `not-found.tsx`, `global-error.tsx`, and any sibling view files like `site-chrome-client.tsx`) must be **pure composition** — import and render components from **`@portfolio/storybook`**, passing data/handlers as props. **Do not** render visible DOM primitives (**`h1`–`h6`**, **`p`**, **`button`**, **`label`**, **`ul`/`ol`/`li`/`dl`**, **`img`**, **`figure`**, **`blockquote`**, **`input`/`select`/`textarea`/`form`**) and **do not** import local **`*.module.css`** files from these files. Structural/landmark elements (**`main`**, **`section`**, **`article`**, **`header`**, **`footer`**, **`nav`**, **`aside`**, **`div`**, **`span`**, **`html`**, **`body`**) are allowed for composition/layout and landmarks. Package CSS subpaths like **`@portfolio/storybook/globals.css`** and **`@portfolio/storybook/layout.module.css`** are allowed (they're owned by the UI package). Both rules are enforced in `apps/frontend/eslint.config.mjs` via **`no-restricted-syntax`** + **`no-restricted-imports`**. If you find yourself reaching for a forbidden primitive or a local CSS module, extract a new component into `packages/storybook/src/<feature>/` (with co-located **`*.module.css`**, story, and `*.stories.test.ts` `play`) and compose it from the app instead. For Next-specific behavior (e.g. `next/link`), accept it via a prop (see the **`SiteShellLinkComponent`** / **`linkComponent`** pattern); for handlers like App Router `reset()`, declare them as action props (see `StatusPageAction`); for slot composition (chrome wrappers, anchored sections), use children/slot props (see **`SiteShell`**, **`HomeResumeAnchor`**).
- For **`apps/frontend/lib/cv-pdf/**`**, keep styles in react-pdf `StyleSheet` files (`styles.ts` / `styles/*.ts`) and do not migrate PDF styles to web CSS.
- **Data fetching**: Prefer server-side fetching in Server Components; use `fetch` caching defaults intentionally. For client mutations, use patterns already present in the repo (e.g. Server Actions, route handlers).
- **Metadata**: Use the Metadata API (`export const metadata` or `generateMetadata`) for SEO and social cards instead of ad-hoc `<head>` manipulation where possible.
- **Imports**: Use path aliases if `tsconfig` defines them; otherwise relative imports — match existing style.
- Run **`yarn lint`** and **`yarn build`** (or project-documented equivalents) after non-trivial changes; see skill `nextjs-change-checklist`.
